<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,151,1365]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,260,285]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The combination of a phallus with two large cornuti, angular transtilla without sublateral processes, gnathos with two rather short caudal processes, wide and short lateral lobes of uncus, very short vinculum, and a golden glossy, grey-brown forewing with an ill-defined postmedian silvery fascia distinguishes 
<taxonomicName box="[1242,1393,332,356]" class="Insecta" family="Nepticulidae" genus="Stigmella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sanmartini" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1242,1393,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">S. sanmartini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="16" pageNumber="17" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
from all other 
<taxonomicName box="[372,477,368,392]" class="Insecta" family="Nepticulidae" genus="Stigmella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[372,477,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Stigmella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, including a few described and undescribed species which trophically are associated with 
<taxonomicName box="[208,331,404,428]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Asteraceae</taxonomicName>
plants and also possess only two cornuti in the male genitalia (also see Discussion).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
